Step 1: Calculate Gross Profit Margin  
 Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
 From the income statement,  
  Gross Profit = 308,309.79  
  Total Revenue = 851,679.79  
 Thus,  
  Gross Profit Margin = (308,309.79 / 851,679.79) × 100 ≈ 36.19%

Step 2: Calculate Operating Cash Flow Ratio  
 Operating Cash Flow Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities)  
 From the cash flow statement and balance sheet,  
  Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -4,510,837.08  
  Total Current Liabilities = 3,376,304.04  
 Thus,  
  Operating Cash Flow Ratio = -4,510,837.08 / 3,376,304.04 ≈ -1.33
